Model performance statistics from Ye et al. 1997

Source: R/YeAl97.R
YeAl97.Rd

Performance statistics from calibrations of three model structures in three catchments in two data periods, assessed using absolute mean deviation, bias and efficiency.

YeAl97

Format

A data frame with 36 observations on the following 7 variables.

Catchment

a character vector, either Canning, Salmon or Stones

calib.period

a character vector, either "First 5Y" or "Second 5Y"

sim.period

a character vector, either "First 5Y" or "Second 5Y"

Model.str

a factor with levels GSFB IHACRES LASCAM

A

a numeric vector, absolute mean deviation

B

a numeric vector, bias

E

a numeric vector, efficiency

Source

Ye, W., B.C. Bates, N.R. Viney, M. Sivapalan and A.J. Jakeman (1997). Performance of conceptual rainfall-runoff models in low-yielding ephemeral catchments. Water Resour. Res. 33(1): 153-166 DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/96wr02840.

References

Used by paretoTimeAnalysis.

data(YeAl97)
